docs.snippet: BLOOM--Fannie, died peacefully at home two weeks before turning 103. Her surviving family, son Lenny and daughter Carol, daughters-in-law Judy and Bracha, granddaughter Jenny, relatives and friends, will cherish her memory. Funeral services will b...
docs.lead_paragraph:
BLOOM--Fannie,

died peacefully at home two weeks before turning 103. Her surviving family, son Lenny and daughter Carol, daughters-in-law Judy and Bracha, granddaughter Jenny, relatives and friends, will cherish her memory. Funeral services will be held at Plaza Funeral Home, 630 Amsterdam Avenue (at West 91st St.) on Tuesday, August 2, at 9:45am. Lenny will sit shiva at 46 West 83rd St. Carol will sit shiva at 2350 Broadway (at West 86th St.) She welcomes visitors from 3-8pm from Wednesday through Friday and on Sunday, 3-8pm.

docs.snippet: WRIGHT--Suzanne. The RiverSpring Health and Hebrew Home at Riverdale families mourn the loss of Suzanne Wright, wife of our dear friend, Bob Wright. Suzanne was one of those rare individuals whose inner drive and determination made a difference an...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WRIGHT--Suzanne.

The RiverSpring Health and Hebrew Home at Riverdale families mourn the loss of Suzanne Wright, wife of our dear friend, Bob Wright. Suzanne was one of those rare individuals whose inner drive and determination made a difference and incited change. Suzanne gave a voice to autism, helping countless families and bringing awareness on a nation level. We extend our heartfelt condolences to the entire Wright family. RiverSpring Health Jeffrey S. Maurer, Chairman Daniel Reingold, President & CEO

Sarah Lawrence College mourns the loss of alumna and honorary trustee Suzanne Werner Wright, whose many contributions to the College included her generous support for the performing arts. We honor her memory and extend condolences to her family. Karen R. Lawrence, President Mark P. Goodman, Chair
